3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper considers a model in which the feed-forward and feedback signals share the same noisy channel, which is a relevant problem in the context of social and information networks. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper does not explicitly deal with computational complexity, but the problem of enhancing secrecy in the wiretap channel is a relevant problem in the context of computational complexity. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper does not deal with multimedia directly, but the techniques used to enhance secrecy in the wiretap channel may have applications in multimedia systems.
